<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,152,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum subquadrate, with denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1326,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); anterior margin of median carina truncated, with perpendicular projection over the head, provided with three protuberances (
<figureCitation box="[160,248,224,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and wavy (two conspicuous curves) (
<figureCitation box="[679,767,224,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
, dorsal view); wings slightly longer than pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="350" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,152,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,677,258,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">
Redescription (Female 
<typeStatus box="[476,580,260,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[592,662,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Body surface rugose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[928,992,260,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Head</emphasis>
. Lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1253,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): head and compound eyes inserted below median carina crest; protuberant and globose eyes with straight base; vertex and fastigium not visible between eyes; antennal groove situated below margin of compound eyes; facial carinae arched. Frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[312,403,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
): fastigium of vertex straight; front hirsute; eyes laterally arranged on the head but not pedunculated; frontal costa inconspicuous, only the bifurcation and facial carina visible; two superior ocelli between facial carina; medial ocellus involved by facial carinae; antennal grooves placed beside facial carinae; antennae shaped as compressed segments laterally expanding from the base to the apex; left antennae missing; apex of each antennal segments with a lighter color than the remaining antenna; scapus and pedicel with small tubercles; maxillary palpi having the two last articles flattened and hirsute. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[971,1061,543,569]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): vertex between eyes wider than eyes in horizontal and vertical diameter; supraocular lobe conspicuous; rectangularly shaped head. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1308,1429,579,605]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Macropronotal, rugose, subquadrate, erose, having irregular teeth and emarginations, with denticles throughout the median carina of pronotum. Lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[677,770,649,676]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
): anterior margin of median carina truncated, with perpendicular projection over the head, provided with three protuberances; median carina crest begins to decline after surpassing the apex of tegmina and then becomes thinner; prozonal carina and extralateral carina inconspicuous; ventral sinus and tegminal sinus present; lateral lobe almost truncated and slightly laterally directed; infrascapular area narrow, thin and shorter than fore tibiae; wings slightly longer than pronotum. Frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1345,791,817]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
): lateral lobes of pronotum slightly projected and directed sideward. Dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[987,1077,827,853]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): median carina continuous and strongly elevated, with crested wavy (two conspicuous curves) (
<figureCitation box="[865,948,862,889]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1814,1839]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,179,1787]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pictorial key to species of Lophotettix. Arrows in L. brevicristatus and L. zumbadoi indicate pronotum direction; in L. unicristatus the arrow points to the hook-like shape of the pronotum and in L. alticristatus and L. hancocki the arrow points to the shape of the anterior margin of the pronotum over the head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491602" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491602/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig.7A</figureCitation>
), lateral lobe almost truncated. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Sternomentum</emphasis>
. Inconspicuous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[390,466,897,924]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Wings</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[489,574,898,925]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig.2A</figureCitation>
): tegmina and wings visible; wing longer than pronotum; tegmina ovoid and elongated with rounded apex; tegmina with slightly marked venation. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[938,1001,933,959]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Legs.</emphasis>
Hirsute. Fore legs (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1347,933,960]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
): dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carinae; tibias with two crests on dorsal margin. Middle legs (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
): left leg missing; dorsal and ventral margins of femur with undulated carina, with a dorso-apical blunt spine; tibiae with two crests on the dorsal margin. Hind legs: both hind legs missing in the type. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1251,1374,1040,1067]" pageId="4" pageNumber="350">Abdomen.</emphasis>
(
